UserComments.Comment:
There is a major problem of non-electric cars using the four spaces provided. I have been in to customer services several times to point this out. Many of the people parking do not realize they are charging spaces, and I have suggested to Waitrose that they paint the spaces more prominently. I don't think my complaints get further than the customer services person though.

Recently, one of two charging posts was out of action. I reported the fault to Chargemaster, but since repair the charger operates only at 3kw - it does not give the usual option of waiting for a fast, 7kw, charge. It seems to have been downgraded. Since the maximum parking in this car park is 2 hours, 3kw is not very useful.

Trouble is, it seems churlish to complain when Waitrose are troubling to provide charging in the first place.

CommentType.Title: Fault Report (Notice To Users And Operator)

UserComments.Comment: Only one out of the four points is working. One post is completely down and the other has a faulty cover on one of the points
Waitrose is a good charge point as my sauce east card works well so i can charge up & shop in the supper store had a successful charge here to day.

needed to try my new ev cable out went to bury st Edmunds to do a bit of shopping at waitrose supper store the charge master charge point was at the back of car park 2 charge master points where on hand i decided to chose the right one as cars where parked in the bays next door as store was busy this was my first time charging at charge master i was using a ev moped in a hurry i forgot my membership & left it at home i went to waitrose customer services to get help staff did help me out & told me to phone support i then went back to charge point then range charge master customer support they helped me get charging then i went to super store to do shopping the staff did all they can to make my shopping experience enjoyable the new cafe was nice as i could take the wait of my feet the staff said it was ok for me to pop into town for a bit so i went to costa just to relax the ev moped was ready to use wen i came back i rang charge master support line they helped me to disc connect wen i disc connected from the ev point i then went home it was a nice day out this charge point works well it is still operational  all charge points very on who owns them charge master did a nice job and it got me going again polar points are good as my card must work on them as well.

UsageCost: Inclusive; for Polar Plus subscription members only

UserComments.Comment: Used 7kw point successfully. Signage is good and there is free parking for 3 hours for charging electric vehicles (both bays as far as I could see).

Used to charge successfully a few times, but been told officially it's only one bay although the post accepts 2 cars charging at the same time & is positioned at the midway point of 2 bays.. not heard of any problems as long as the cars plugged in :)
Charged 3 times here now. Bays are now marked and parking enforcement in place.

In a central car park, but signage is faulty - could be used in an emergency, if you stay with the vehicle. The "Electric Only" sign faces the wrong way into the entry lane, which is clearly marked "NO PARKING". The adjacent bays are not marked and always full. This should be corrected at some point but is waiting for a new traffic order and new signage.

UserComments.Comment: 9 times out of 10 there's an ice vehicle in the way, if anyone else finds this go in and complain, if we all do this they might just do something about it so we can access the charging point... Which is becoming more important in Bedford as electric car ownership is growing & now find I have to drive round to find a free space..

My second attempt to charge. After previous complaints, the signs have been turned round the correct way, but no floor marking present so both bays ICEd. There is very little visitor parking, so this is always going to be case - effectively these bays will always be blocked, although they may well be worth trying out-of-hours. If they are ICEd, then there is another charging point on the same side of the road about 100 metres further on immediately in the entrance to Bedford College.

Surely if you want to encourage commuters to use EVs there needs to be more thought than this and definitely more points.  Bedford you are way behind milton keynes on this front.

UserComments.Comment: I’ve been in to the Green label car park twice in the last 2 weeks and on both occasions the charge stations have been closed. They even have a notice on the ticket machine when entering the car park.
Having not charged on Sat 4th, was able to charge today. Very pleased. Easy to use. Staff helpful when call upon.
Looks like it's working, but on speaking to car park attendant, they haven't been working for a day or so. All set up to work and simple to use, bit disappointed, looking forward to using next time

On arrival 3 bays empty, 3 bays closed. Service wasn't operational. Called through to Queensgate Customer Services who were able to reset the system. On return to the vehicle later that afternoon somebody had removed our charging cable from the point, less than 20 mins into the charge! Result - not enough charge for the journey home, had to wait to recharge : /  .. NOTE TO PROVIDER: as with the 'car end' and other charging stations, please update the hardware to lock the cable when in use!
Works fantastic! I'm a new EV owner and this is easy to operate and there are plenty of spaces.
